Position Description The Senior Research Scientist provides analysis, leadership and support for scientific studies, contract deliverables, data requests, and database maintenance activities utilizing the OPTN database, research analysis datasets and other sources of data as necessary. The current vacancy would be best filled some someone with an established history of obtaining and executing grant-funded research and an extensive track record of peer reviewed publication. Key Responsibilities: · Serves as subject matter expert in one or more areas: organ-specific research; transplantation systems; donor and/or OPO programs; immunosuppression; transplantation outcomes; performance analysis; research methodology; or transplantation finances.  · Participate in business development activities including meeting with prospective clients, identifying strategic opportunities in areas of value and work with teams to market those opportunities.  · Designs and conducts quantitative and qualitative research in the field of organ transplantation in order to complete contract deliverables and other special project of scientific value.  · Responsible for the development, direction and execution of research studies related to OPTN committees or other scientific inquiry. · Serve as primary interface with organ-specific OPTN committees. Provide analytical support and respond to requests from committees.  · Directs the work of research analysts in support of committee work and other scientific inquiry studies. Mentors the Research Analysts Lead and manage highly complex transplantation-related projects for both committee and non-committee related activities.  · Research highly complex health issues and review published literature for opportunities for new advances in transplantation knowledge.  · Lead project teams and monitor project costs · Plan/direct the preparation of proposals of significant technical complexity, contract value or strategic importance.  · Direct and oversee information gathering; review technical data and information summaries.  · Collaborate with other researchers and transplantation professionals on presentations and publications  · Collaborate with Philanthropy team to identify research projects ripe for grant funding and work together to seek out and apply for grant funded opportunities. · Other duties as assigned.  Minimum Requirements · PhD with 8 years of related research experience (to include Graduate Assistant work) required. Also will consider a Master’s degree with 6+ years of professional work experience.  Critical Skills · Basic competence in R, SQL, and SAS programming is preferred.  · Foundational knowledge of modeling paradigms and complexity theory · Strong research skills · Must have ability/experience in writing grants and contract proposals.  · Must have demonstrated ability to do independent research · Ability to work effectively in a team environment  · Must have excellent oral and written communication skills. · Must be self-motivated and able to work independently and within teams. · Design and development of simulation models from subject matter expert specifications · Qualitative or quantitative data collection and analysis · Must have demonstrated ability to do independent research. Additional Skills and Qualifications · 5 years of experience in healthcare research is preferred. · 8 years of epidemiology, bioinformatics or other related research experience required. · Experience in developing and leading research/analytical studies is preferred. Education Advanced degree in Statistics, Biostatistics,
Bioinformatics, Epidemiology, Public Health, Health Services Research or other
related field of study, or equivalent level of research experience
required. PhD is highly desired. Physical Requirements · General office demands · Some overnight travel
